benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: PUT /1.0/kb/accounts/{accountId}/customFields - Modify custom fields to account

covered: PUT Valid Requests: TC01, TC02, TC03, TC04, TC15, TC16, TC17, TC24 show successful updates across typical and edge-case scenarios.
Validation and Error Handling: TC06, TC07, TC08, TC09, TC10, TC11, TC18 cover invalid inputs, missing headers, missing body, malformed JSON, and invalid CustomField schemas.
Authorization: TC12 validates unauthorized access; TC08 also validates missing required header.
Resilience and error handling: TC13 (503), TC14 (502), TC19 (504), TC22 (transient network recovery) test service reliability and error scenarios.
Security and data integrity: TC20 (SQL injection), TC21 (XSS), TC23 (duplicate field names) test input sanitization and data integrity.
Performance and integration: TC25 (concurrency across accounts), TC26 (payload size near limit), TC27 (audit logs integration), TC28 (external reporting data consistency).
Accessibility and documentation: TC29 ensures accessibility of API docs and error messages.
Edge-case robustness: TC15 empty array, TC16 max values, TC17 extra properties ignored, TC23 duplicate names represent robustness to edge inputs.
gaps: Partial Update: No explicit test confirming whether partial updates are accepted or rejected; PUT semantics here are not clearly tested.
Rate limiting: No tests for rate limiting or throttling behavior.
Caching behavior: No tests for ETag/Cache-Control or caching semantics.
Non-existent resource error code consistency: TC07 uses 400 for non-existent account; consider 404 Not Found for consistency.
Same-resource concurrency: No test explicitly addressing race conditions on updates to the same account.
recommendations: Add a Partial Update test to confirm behavior when only a subset of fields is provided.
Add rate-limiting tests to verify throttling under high load.
Add caching tests to verify ETag/Cache-Control headers and caching behavior.
Consider aligning non-existent resource error codes to 404 and add a 403 Forbidden test for insufficient permissions if applicable.
Add a dedicated test for same-resource race conditions to improve concurrency coverage.
